>>>>---- CRON ----<<<<<

Add a New Cron Job

Cron jobs follow this format:

MIN HOUR DOM MON DOW COMMAND

    MIN → Minute (0–59)
    HOUR → Hour (0–23)
    DOM → Day of Month (1–31)
    MON → Month (1–12)
    DOW → Day of Week (0–7, where both 0 and 7 mean Sunday)
    COMMAND → The command/script to run

3. Example: Log Network Usage with vnstat

Let’s say you want to log daily bandwidth usage to a file at midnight:

0 0 * * * vnstat -m > ~/vnstat_monthly_usage.log

crontab -e (edit cronjobs)
crontab -l (list cronjobs)







NETWORK MONITORS

-- vnstat -d (day) -m (month) -i <network interface code> (spec interface inspect)

-- bmon - bandwith monitor -  -p eth0 (real-time monitoring of traffic on port eth0)
